{"type":"message","id":"3caed111","parentId":"b5d915ad","timestamp":"2026-03-24T15:15:12.603Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_0wih0frumeza_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 111416\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the state and decide on the best concrete action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals and recent work:\r\n1. CFI analysis is complete - found that 44.8% of invariants are pure noise (CFI=0), only 5.7% are true causal anchors (CFI>=0.7)\r\n2. Next pending action: CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline)\r\n\r\nThe key insight from CFI_RESULTS.md is:\r\n- Two types of persistence: Process (CFI=0, metaprogramming artifacts) vs Research Trajectory (CFI>0.7, causal)\r\n- We need to distinguish \"constant format\" (freq=60, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<60, CFI>0.7)\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step is to run the CFI-weighted compression experiment. This means:\r\n1. Take the existing pulse text invariants\r\n2. Create a CFI-weighted version that prioritizes high-CFI invariants\r\n3. Compare next-pulse prediction accuracy vs frequency baseline\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist and what I need to create. The CFI_RESULTS.md has the raw data. I should create a script or document that:\r\n1. Loads the CFI results\r\n2. Creates CFI-weighted compression\r\n3. Compares against frequency baseline\r\n\r\nActually, looking more carefully - I need to implement the experiment. The most concrete action would be to create a script that performs this comparison, or create a new document that outlines the experimental design.\r\n\r\nLet me check what's in the research directory... Based on the context, I have:\r\n- research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md\r\n- research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md\r\n- research/CFI_RESULTS.md (recently created)\r\n\r\nThe pending action is to run the CFI-weighted compression experiment. A concrete action would be to create a Python script or PowerShell script that:\r\n\r\n\r\nI'll design an experimental script that rigorously compares CFI-weighted compression against the frequency baseline. The script will extract high-impact invariants, generate compressed representations, and systematically validate prediction performance. This approach will provide a clear, quantifiable measure of the CFI method's effectiveness in capturing meaningful research trajectory information.\r\n\r\nThe key will be developing a robust experimental framework that can precisely measure the differential impact of CFI-weighting on compression and prediction accuracy. By creating a structured comparison methodology, I can empirically validate the theoretical insights from the CFI_RESULTS.md analysis.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI analysis reveals that frequency-based compression loses ~82% of signal (mean CFI=0.181). The critical next step is to empirically validate that CFI-weighted compression outperforms frequency baseline for next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the CFI-weighted compression experiment script that compares CFI-based vs frequency-based compression quality for next-pulse prediction. This is the most direct test of whether CFI filtering is worth implementing.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n## Comparing CFI vs Frequency for Next-Pulse Prediction\r\n\r\n**Created:** 2026-03-24\r\n**Status:** EXPERIMENTAL\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCFI-weighted compression will yield higher next-pulse prediction accuracy than frequency-weighted compression, because it preserves causal invariants rather than metaprogramming artifacts.\r\n\r\n## Method\r\n\r\n### Dataset\r\n- Source: `research/CFI_RESULTS.md` invariant data\r\n- Filter: Only invariants with CFI >= 0.3 (probable causal)\r\n- Baseline: All invariants (including CFI=0 noise)\r\n\r\n### Compression Methods\r\n\r\n| Method | Weight Formula | Rationale |\r\n|--------|----------------|-----------|\r\n| Frequency | `weight = freq` | Original baseline |\r\n| CFI | `weight = CFI` | Prioritize causal invariants |\r\n| Hybrid | `weight = freq * CFI` | Balance frequency and causality |\r\n| Log-Freq + CFI | `weight = log(freq) + CFI` | Dampen high-frequency dominance |\r\n\r\n### Prediction Task\r\nFor each pulse `P[i]`, predict whether invariants in `P[i+1]` are present in compressed representation of `P[i]`.\r\n\r\n### Metrics\r\n- **Precision@K:** Fraction of predicted invariants that appear in next pulse\r\n- **Recall@K:** Fraction of next-pulse invariants captured in prediction\r\n- **Overlap Rate:** Raw invariant overlap between consecutive pulses\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\n```python\r\nimport json\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\n\r\n# Load CFI results\r\ncfi_data = json.loads(Path(\"research/CFI_RESULTS.md\").read_text())\r\n\r\n# Extract invariant table\r\ninvariants = cfi_data[\"invariant_table\"]  # list of {freq, cfi, ...}\r\n\r\n# Filter by CFI threshold\r\ncausal_invariants = [inv for inv in invariants if inv[\"cfi\"] >= 0.3]\r\n\r\n# Generate compressed representations\r\ndef compress(invariants, method=\"cfi\"):\r\n    weights = []\r\n    for inv in invariants:\r\n        if method == \"freq\":\r\n            w = inv[\"freq\"]\r\n        elif method == \"cfi\":\r\n            w = inv[\"cfi\"]\r\n        elif method == \"hybrid\":\r\n            w = inv[\"freq\"] * inv[\"cfi\"]\r\n        elif method == \"log_cfi\":\r\n            import math\r\n            w = math.log(inv[\"freq\"] + 1) + inv[\"cfi\"]\r\n        weights.append((inv, w))\r\n    \r\n    # Sort by weight descending, take top N\r\n    weights.sort(key=lambda x: -x[1])\r\n    return weights\r\n\r\n# Compare methods\r\nmethods = [\"freq\", \"cfi\", \"hybrid\", \"log_cfi\"]\r\nK_VALUES = [5, 10, 20, 50]\r\n\r\nfor method in methods:\r\n\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 11:14:47\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774365312600}}
